From 3ef6ea2acc90830b514debb79afb7ced9d2eac86 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ripan Deuri <rdeuri@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 25 May 2025 18:16:57 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Fix num_tx_pending for multicast
 packet

In multicast packet handling, the 'ar' pointer is not updated in the copied skb->cb,
resulting in incorrect accounting of num_tx_pending.

Set 'ar' field in skb->cb after skb_copy() to fix the issue.

Patch-dependency: 0113-0007-wifi-ath12k-Refactor-data-path-pdev-struct.patch
Signed-off-by: Ripan Deuri <rdeuri@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
@@ -1043,6 +1043,7 @@ static void ath12k_wifi7_mac_op_tx(struc
 			skb_cb = ATH12K_SKB_CB(msdu_copied);
 			skb_cb->link_id = link_id;
 			skb_cb->vif = vif;
+			skb_cb->u.ar = tmp_ar;
 
 			if (ahsta && ahsta->use_4addr_set)
 				arsta = rcu_dereference(ahsta->link[link_id]);
